  "description": "CS-NRRM is a continuity-aware longitudinal observation framework built upon approximately 12 years (4,300 days) of creator-maintained human chronology documented by Changhun Shin. The framework does not function as a predictive AI model, medical diagnostic engine, or automated treatment system. Instead, it organizes continuity-preserved observational records into machine-readable chronological structures designed for continuity-aware interpretation and longitudinal archival preservation within a strictly non-medical and descriptive boundary.",
